From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: PanicOS <panicos@localhost>
Date: Sun, 25 May 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: sun4i-codec: fix H616 internal codec half-speed audio

The H616 internal codec I2S interface has two hardware-fixed behaviours
that the generic sun4i_codec_get_mod_freq() path does not account for:

  1. BCLK is generated at MCLK/16 (fixed ratio, not auto-adapting like
     H3/A33).
  2. The I2S interface always uses 32-bit slots regardless of the
     logical sample format (S16_LE or S32_LE).  params_physical_width()
     returns 16 for S16_LE, but the hardware clocks 64 BCLK pulses per
     LRCLK period in both cases.

With MCLK = 24576000 Hz (what get_mod_freq returns for 48 kHz):

  BCLK  = 24576000 / 16        = 1 536 000 Hz
  LRCLK = 1 536 000 / 64       =    24 000 Hz  ← half of target 48 kHz

This produces audio that plays at exactly half speed with the wrong
pitch, for both S16_LE and S32_LE.  The symptom appeared once AHUB DTS
nodes were enabled (PipeWire then negotiated S32_LE with the codec),
but both formats were broken.

Fix: add two new quirk fields:

  fixed_bclk_div   — hardware BCLK = MCLK / fixed_bclk_div
  i2s_slot_width   — physical I2S slot width in bits (0 → params_physical_width)

In sun4i_codec_probe(), after the quirks pointer is available, precompute
mclk_mult = i2s_slot_width × 2 × fixed_bclk_div and store it in the
sun4i_codec instance.  sun4i_codec_hw_params() then uses:

  MCLK = params_rate(params) × mclk_mult

giving the correct MCLK for any sample rate or format:

  48 kHz  → 48000  × 1024 = 49 152 000 Hz  (pll-audio-2x)
  44.1 kHz → 44100 × 1024 = 45 158 400 Hz  (pll-audio-2x·44.1)

When mclk_mult is zero (all other chips) the legacy get_mod_freq() path
is used unchanged.

Measured before fix: hw_ptr advanced ~24 120 frames/s (≈ 0.5×) at 48 kHz.
After fix: 48 000 frames/s.

Signed-off-by: PanicOS <panicos@localhost>
---
 sound/soc/sunxi/sun4i-codec.c | 42 ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++------
 1 file changed, 35 insertions(+), 7 deletions(-)

diff --git a/sound/soc/sunxi/sun4i-codec.c b/sound/soc/sunxi/sun4i-codec.c
index 111111111111..222222222222 100644
--- a/sound/soc/sunxi/sun4i-codec.c
+++ b/sound/soc/sunxi/sun4i-codec.c
@@ -342,6 +342,10 @@ struct sun4i_codec {
 	struct snd_dmaengine_dai_dma_data	capture_dma_data;
 	struct snd_dmaengine_dai_dma_data	playback_dma_data;
+
+	/* mclk_mult != 0: MCLK = rate * mclk_mult (H616 fixed-ratio path).
+	 * 0 means use the legacy sun4i_codec_get_mod_freq() table. */
+	u32 mclk_mult;
 };

@@ -2149,6 +2153,15 @@ struct sun4i_codec_quirks {
 	bool has_reset;
 	bool playback_only;
 	u32 dma_max_burst;
+	/* If non-zero, BCLK is generated at MCLK/fixed_bclk_div by the hardware.
+	 * i2s_slot_width gives the physical I2S slot width in bits (0 = use
+	 * params_physical_width).  hw_params sets:
+	 *   MCLK = rate * slot_width * 2 * fixed_bclk_div
+	 * When 0 the legacy sun4i_codec_get_mod_freq() path is used instead. */
+	u8 fixed_bclk_div;
+	u8 i2s_slot_width;
 };

@@ -2241,6 +2254,10 @@ static const struct sun4i_codec_quirks sun50i_h616_codec_quirks = {
 	.has_reset	= true,
 	.dma_max_burst	= SUN4I_DMA_MAX_BURST,
+	/* H616 codec I2S: BCLK = MCLK/16 (hardware fixed), slot width always
+	 * 32 bits.  MCLK = rate*32*2*16 = rate*1024 → 49152000 Hz at 48 kHz. */
+	.fixed_bclk_div	= 16,
+	.i2s_slot_width	= 32,
 };

@@ -2330,6 +2347,12 @@ static int sun4i_codec_probe(struct platform_device *pdev)
 		return -ENODEV;
 	}

+	if (quirks->fixed_bclk_div) {
+		unsigned int sw = quirks->i2s_slot_width ?: 16;
+		scodec->mclk_mult = sw * 2 * quirks->fixed_bclk_div;
+	}
+
 	scodec->regmap = devm_regmap_init_mmio(&pdev->dev, base,

@@ -2659,11 +2682,16 @@ static int sun4i_codec_hw_params(struct snd_pcm_substream *substream,
 {
 	struct snd_soc_pcm_runtime *rtd = snd_soc_substream_to_rtd(substream);
 	struct sun4i_codec *scodec = snd_soc_card_get_drvdata(rtd->card);
-	unsigned long clk_freq;
+	unsigned long clk_freq;
 	int ret, hwrate;

-	clk_freq = sun4i_codec_get_mod_freq(params);
-	if (!clk_freq)
-		return -EINVAL;
+	if (scodec->mclk_mult) {
+		clk_freq = (unsigned long)params_rate(params) * scodec->mclk_mult;
+	} else {
+		clk_freq = sun4i_codec_get_mod_freq(params);
+		if (!clk_freq)
+			return -EINVAL;
+	}

 	ret = clk_set_rate(scodec->clk_module, clk_freq);
 	if (ret)
--
